Uh, I-I-I teach.

04:04.920 --> 04:07.254
I-I used to be a teacher.

04:07.255 --> 04:11.025
Now, I mainly... I mainly teach teachers.

04:11.026 --> 04:12.784
I... I teach teachers...

04:13.776 --> 04:15.143
teaching.

04:15.144 --> 04:16.635
Do you enjoy it?

04:16.660 --> 04:18.978
It's a job.

04:18.980 --> 04:21.851
I-I need ice.

04:24.554 --> 04:27.022
I think your fridge is not working

04:27.023 --> 04:29.759
or maybe just empty.

04:33.752 --> 04:37.752
Milo is in-in Guatemala, in which town?

04:38.222 --> 04:40.194
He didn't say.

04:43.225 --> 04:45.760
But you asked him.

04:47.562 --> 04:50.964
I don't remember the name,
but yeah, yeah, we asked him.

04:50.965 --> 04:53.763
No, we did not ask because
it's none of our business.

04:54.369 --> 04:55.420
Mm-hmm.

04:57.444 --> 05:01.138
Milo's business is in real estate, right?

05:01.303 --> 05:03.783
Yes, buying and selling property.

05:03.784 --> 05:06.016
- That is all he does.
- No.

05:06.017 --> 05:08.931
Milo has his fingers in a lot of pies.

05:09.533 --> 05:10.667
Which pies?

05:10.668 --> 05:13.736
Hmm, investments, stock speculations.

05:13.737 --> 05:17.707
Uh, he and I both, uh,
play the markets a little.

05:17.708 --> 05:21.708
Stock market? No.
No, just, uh, real estate.

05:25.504 --> 05:28.973
Which of you would you say is...

05:28.974 --> 05:30.989
is closest to Milo?

05:32.388 --> 05:35.290
I guess, I am. I mean,
I've known him the longest.

05:35.291 --> 05:38.460
- Lex.
- Lex.

05:38.461 --> 05:41.270
- Me.
- And you, what do you do?

05:41.575 --> 05:42.676
I deal in antiques.

05:42.903 --> 05:45.905
And up until a few years ago,
I practiced law

05:45.906 --> 05:48.975
and I'm pretty sure this right here,

05:48.976 --> 05:51.683
without a warrant, not exactly legal.

05:51.934 --> 05:53.201
You know about law.

05:53.202 --> 05:54.721
That's what I just said.

05:54.722 --> 05:56.739
You rented a car.

06:00.377 --> 06:02.612
- From the airport.
- Yes.

06:05.166 --> 06:07.968
So where is it? I didn't see it outside.

06:07.969 --> 06:11.969
Well, um, we drove into
town last night and, uh,

06:12.573 --> 06:16.573
got a little drunk so, um,
we left it in town,

06:17.140 --> 06:18.389
took a taxi back.

06:19.223 --> 06:21.258
So where-where is the car?

06:24.915 --> 06:26.332
The craziest thing.

06:26.333 --> 06:30.320
Uh, we can't really remember where it is

06:30.321 --> 06:32.322
because we got pretty drunk.

06:34.090 --> 06:35.600
We had a good time.

06:36.727 --> 06:39.701
Would you like us to find it?

06:40.202 --> 06:41.669
No, no, that's fine.

06:41.670 --> 06:43.805
We have an idea where,
I think I know the street.

06:43.806 --> 06:45.907
It's got... there's a gas station that's...

06:45.908 --> 06:48.410
It's-it's very easy, very easy.

06:48.411 --> 06:51.480
No, it's fine. We'll get it. Thank you.

06:52.415 --> 06:54.717
Your name and address, please.

06:58.033 --> 06:59.133
How about this?

06:59.134 --> 07:03.134
How about you, uh, you write down your name

07:04.212 --> 07:07.046
and badge number and your superior's name?

07:07.047 --> 07:11.047
Because where I'm from,
this is not how it's done.

07:12.052 --> 07:15.090
You know what, if you're
going to question us,

07:15.091 --> 07:16.490
I think we should have a lawyer

07:16.491 --> 07:18.004
or somebody from the embassy present.

07:18.156 --> 07:20.825
I thought your-your friend
used to be a lawyer.

07:20.826 --> 07:22.493
Gus, right.

07:22.494 --> 07:25.397
I'm not sure I want to take
legal advice from him.

07:28.328 --> 07:32.328
Why you think you need to call a lawyer?

07:32.966 --> 07:35.169
Have you done something wrong?

07:36.960 --> 07:38.110
No.

07:38.638 --> 07:42.441
We're four friends on vacation.

07:42.442 --> 07:45.245
And you're very close.

07:47.314 --> 07:49.818
Yep, super tight.

07:50.195 --> 07:51.450
No.

07:51.655 --> 07:53.341
Some of us are closer than others.

07:53.912 --> 07:57.481
Close? Us?

07:58.817 --> 08:01.998
Okay. We know you have plane reservations,

08:02.085 --> 08:03.318
leave on Monday night,

08:03.319 --> 08:06.621
the 6:00 PM flight via Houston.

08:06.622 --> 08:07.944
You tell her that, too, Gus?

08:07.975 --> 08:09.924
While we continue our investigation,

08:09.925 --> 08:11.921
I must ask you not
to leave Belize before then.

08:12.053 --> 08:13.520
What if we do?

08:14.163 --> 08:15.702
You will be detained at the airport.

08:15.867 --> 08:19.570
Why? Because of some missing
boat we know nothing about?

08:19.806 --> 08:21.243
How can I explain?

08:22.025 --> 08:24.149
You're not in the United States.

08:24.494 --> 08:28.494
The person the boat
belongs to is very savage.

08:28.721 --> 08:30.222
We are trying to solve a crime,

08:30.223 --> 08:31.958
but we are also trying to protect

08:31.959 --> 08:33.525
whoever stole the boat

08:33.525 --> 08:36.227
because clearly they do not
understand what they did.

08:36.229 --> 08:37.589
Must be worth a lot of money then.

08:37.799 --> 08:39.500
Jesús is a man of principle.

08:39.501 --> 08:42.870
Whether he's owed a lot or a
little, he will seek atonement.

08:42.871 --> 08:46.240
Doesn't matter if
the person is here in Belize

08:46.241 --> 08:47.690
or even in the United States.

08:47.715 --> 08:50.245
He has many associates.

08:51.721 --> 08:55.225
When Milo returns, ask him to call me.

09:00.841 --> 09:04.811
Ay, and don't worry, Lex,

09:04.812 --> 09:06.914
I'll find your car.

09:35.270 --> 09:37.136
What's she talking about, find our car?

09:37.161 --> 09:38.964
She saw the rental car keys on the table.

09:38.965 --> 09:40.746
- She asked where it was.
- What'd you say?

09:40.771 --> 09:42.489
- I said we lost it.
- Why'd you say that?

09:42.528 --> 09:44.536
I didn't know what to say
so I said we didn't know

09:44.513 --> 09:46.018
where it was.
Who are you calling? Who are you calling?

09:46.043 --> 09:47.309
Operator, I would like to be connected

09:47.310 --> 09:48.729
to the American embassy, please.

09:48.730 --> 09:51.103
By the way, who opened up the damn gate?

09:51.104 --> 09:52.275
I did.

09:52.300 --> 09:54.080
Oh, of course you did.
Why doesn't that surprise me?

09:54.237 --> 09:55.736
I'm sorry, what are you trying to say, Gus?

09:55.737 --> 09:57.807
I'm saying that for as
long as we've known you,

09:57.808 --> 10:00.009
you've always been the one
to do retarded shit like that

10:00.010 --> 10:01.645
that we...

10:03.647 --> 10:05.047
...have to clean up.

10:05.048 --> 10:07.884
We heard everything you were saying to her.

10:07.885 --> 10:11.253
What-what... you-you-you-you
think that I was...

10:11.254 --> 10:13.297
English.

10:13.416 --> 10:15.350
Option one.

10:15.351 --> 10:17.908
They're closed. Want me to leave a message.

10:17.909 --> 10:19.658
Then leave one. Leave one.

10:19.659 --> 10:21.691
Okay, My-my name is...

10:21.692 --> 10:22.925
Don't...

10:22.926 --> 10:24.526
I'm an American citizen.

10:24.527 --> 10:28.497
Uh, I-I came here with a friend-a friend...

10:28.498 --> 10:30.266
Wait...

10:31.257 --> 10:34.759
There was this-this cat.

10:34.760 --> 10:35.807
How the hell am I going
to explain this shit?

10:35.808 --> 10:37.307
Wait a second, wait a second.

10:37.354 --> 10:39.430
She's just gone to...

10:39.431 --> 10:40.705
to look for a car rented in our names.

10:40.940 --> 10:41.471
My name.

10:41.628 --> 10:45.628
With millions of euros of
drug money sitting in the trunk.

10:54.141 --> 10:57.778
Do you realize we have less

10:57.779 --> 10:59.914
than four hours to return the boat?

11:13.533 --> 11:16.135
Hey, I-I don't-I don't
know if you remember me...

11:16.136 --> 11:17.414
You don't think I remember you?

11:17.439 --> 11:19.273
Yeah, I-I rented a car from you earlier.

11:19.274 --> 11:21.608
I misplaced the keys and I was wondering

11:21.609 --> 11:22.944
if you had an extra set.

11:22.945 --> 11:26.945
I'll put it on your bill.

11:28.944 --> 11:32.944
So, um, what was all this retarded shit

11:33.616 --> 11:35.669
you had to clean up? I'm-I'm curious.

11:37.224 --> 11:39.364
Really? Right here.

11:39.427 --> 11:40.497
Why not?

11:42.060 --> 11:43.962
Totaling a friend's motorcycle

11:43.963 --> 11:46.921
and asking us to lie and
say that it was stolen.

11:46.922 --> 11:48.297
Asking us to cover for you

11:48.298 --> 11:50.774
because you're too damn
hungover to make it to class.

11:50.775 --> 11:54.775
Asking us to lend you our
CDs and clothes and-and-

11:55.309 --> 11:56.444
and-and apartments
knowing that

11:56.445 --> 11:59.295
it'd probably end up trashed or lost.

11:59.320 --> 12:01.654
- Vouching for you.
- Vouching for me. Wow.

12:01.655 --> 12:04.691
Interesting that you'd bring
that up 'cause here's

12:04.692 --> 12:07.427
a vouch I can think of that
didn't exactly pan out for me.

12:07.428 --> 12:08.928
Don't you think we
have more pressing things

12:08.929 --> 12:10.630
to deal with right now?

12:10.631 --> 12:13.600
Like getting the boat back
or dealing with this damn car

12:13.601 --> 12:15.252
that you just alerted the police to?

12:15.669 --> 12:16.854
Thank you.

12:17.839 --> 12:20.157
Southside Construction ring any bells?

12:20.158 --> 12:21.642
- What?
- You don't remember?

12:21.643 --> 12:22.810
I was in line for a management gig.

12:22.811 --> 12:24.278
I aced the interviews, then I asked you for

12:24.279 --> 12:26.180
a letter of recommendation
because you knew them.

12:26.181 --> 12:28.482
Yes, they were clients.
I gave them a letter.

12:28.483 --> 12:30.786
Got it, guys, let's go.

12:41.296 --> 12:43.097
Well, this doesn't look suspicious.

12:43.098 --> 12:44.531
Exactly, so let's hurry it up.

12:44.532 --> 12:46.000
Is it just me or does it bother anyone else

12:46.001 --> 12:47.094
that this money is short?

12:47.133 --> 12:48.493
Does it bother anyone else that Jesús

12:48.494 --> 12:49.829
has associates in the U.S.?

12:49.830 --> 12:51.289
Does it bother anybody else that the cops

12:51.314 --> 12:52.641
may show up at any moment?

12:52.673 --> 12:53.790
How much did you give fender bender woman?

12:53.869 --> 12:55.804
I didn't give fender bender woman anything.

12:55.805 --> 12:57.471
- She took it.
- How much?

12:57.472 --> 13:00.108
Uh, uh, a stack. At least a full stack.

13:00.109 --> 13:01.642
- I saw that.
- That's ten grand.

13:01.643 --> 13:04.625
We are not giving this
money back ten grand short.

13:04.626 --> 13:06.815
Follow me, please.

13:16.141 --> 13:18.397
Jerk.

13:31.143 --> 13:33.524
Hey, do you think Milo
knew what might happen

13:33.549 --> 13:35.079
when he invited us here?

13:35.111 --> 13:36.812
I wouldn't put it past him
to take us all down with him.

13:36.813 --> 13:38.032
No, no.

13:38.064 --> 13:39.529
I-I think it was a cry for help.

13:39.530 --> 13:41.498
I think he knew he was
in trouble, he was scared.

13:41.499 --> 13:44.068
He wanted his homies around him.

13:44.069 --> 13:46.270
Yeah, like I'm his homie.

13:46.271 --> 13:48.306
Where's he going?

13:50.767 --> 13:53.503
Why are we stopping?
Where's he going?

13:56.606 --> 13:58.174
Two minutes.

13:58.175 --> 14:00.143
I'm not here to cause
any distress or trouble,

14:00.144 --> 14:02.646
but I think it's important
you hear what I have to say.

14:04.181 --> 14:06.216
What the fuck is he doing?

14:09.386 --> 14:12.241
Oh, I think he's putting the squeeze

14:12.242 --> 14:13.280
on fender bender woman.

14:13.499 --> 14:14.999
I know you're not stupid.

14:15.000 --> 14:16.767
You know what that cash is about.

14:16.768 --> 14:18.569
I'm not here to pretend
that it's something else,

14:18.570 --> 14:22.570
but my concern is with that cash
comes a whole lot of trouble.

14:23.161 --> 14:25.910
This concern, it's for you or for me?

14:25.911 --> 14:28.703
For both. Look, I'm not a criminal.

14:28.704 --> 14:30.750
My buddies out there are not criminals.

14:30.751 --> 14:32.102
You think I couldn't tell that?

14:32.439 --> 14:35.675
Somehow we stumbled into
this cosmic fuck up

14:35.676 --> 14:36.862
and for whatever crazy ass reason,

14:36.863 --> 14:38.401
you've stumbled into it, too.

14:39.144 --> 14:41.612
I'm sorry, but if you don't
give back that cash,

14:41.613 --> 14:44.028
I promise you that we are both in danger.

14:47.118 --> 14:48.372
That's all I got.

14:56.095 --> 14:58.129
She's giving us back the money.

14:58.130 --> 14:58.994
- What?
- What?

14:59.019 --> 15:00.356
Wha...

15:02.960 --> 15:03.764
All right, I'm going with him.

15:03.765 --> 15:05.194
Wait, I don't think this
is such a good idea.

15:05.233 --> 15:07.832
You don't even know where you're going.

15:08.733 --> 15:10.801
Okay, we'll wait here.

15:19.610 --> 15:21.310
Coming to give me backup?

15:21.311 --> 15:23.615
Yeah, just like you
did when I needed that job.

15:23.616 --> 15:24.718
That was four fucking years ago.

15:24.719 --> 15:26.054
I know exactly when it was.

15:26.148 --> 15:28.850
I-I had a deposit on an
apartment, which I lost.

15:28.851 --> 15:30.419
Was gonna get a company car,

15:30.420 --> 15:32.120
had an opportunity to get my shit together

15:32.121 --> 15:34.175
after Kayla and all the other
crap that went down,

15:34.200 --> 15:37.426
and all I needed from... Aah! Ick.

15:37.427 --> 15:39.629
Mind the open sewer.

15:40.237 --> 15:41.404
Fuck!

15:49.872 --> 15:51.331
Okay.

15:52.141 --> 15:54.275
You know what I think we should do?

15:54.276 --> 15:56.643
Go sit outside the embassy

15:56.644 --> 15:58.097
and wait for it to open.

16:00.082 --> 16:04.082
And just leave them here?
What, what do you mean?

16:04.139 --> 16:08.139
Well, obviously wait for them to come back.

16:11.768 --> 16:14.537
Assuming they do come back.

16:25.918 --> 16:28.722
- All I needed was a letter.
- I gave them one.

16:28.723 --> 16:30.203
- Is that right?
- I wrote the letter.

16:30.243 --> 16:32.978
- I should know, Lex.
- And what did you say?

16:33.089 --> 16:34.489
I'm-I'm very curious.

16:34.551 --> 16:36.186
I said the typical shit that you would say

16:36.211 --> 16:38.011
in those kinds of letters.

16:38.410 --> 16:40.244
- We're here.
- Come in.

16:51.488 --> 16:53.222
Hi. Sorry.

16:53.223 --> 16:54.313
- Hey.
- Shut up now.

16:54.314 --> 16:56.892
Hello. Sorry.

16:56.893 --> 16:58.662
Grans?

17:04.111 --> 17:06.646
Shaved ice, cool you down, man?

17:06.646 --> 17:08.782
Uh, hey, we don't have any money so, uh,

17:08.784 --> 17:10.916
why don't you just leave?

17:10.917 --> 17:13.921
Uh, seriously, we don't have any cash.

17:16.915 --> 17:19.184
Here you go, a present from Belize.

17:20.819 --> 17:23.422
- Take care, man.
- Thank you.

17:37.275 --> 17:38.538
Good.

17:45.194 --> 17:46.528
Do you have any idea

17:46.529 --> 17:47.482
what ten grand would mean to these people?

17:47.686 --> 17:50.084
Do you have any idea how much
my hands and feet mean to me?

17:51.218 --> 17:54.287
My roof you're under! In my house!

17:55.094 --> 17:56.528
Grans!

18:01.200 --> 18:02.601
- Did you get it?
- Yeah.

18:02.602 --> 18:03.734
- No.
- Most of it.

18:03.735 --> 18:05.241
- She gave us $6,500.
- What do you mean?

18:05.242 --> 18:07.187
Her grandmother spent the rest.

18:07.188 --> 18:08.214
Oh, bullshit!

18:08.847 --> 18:10.247
No, I don't-I don't buy it.

18:10.248 --> 18:12.749
Did you-did you threaten her, huh?

18:12.750 --> 18:14.517
What are you guys, men?

18:14.518 --> 18:15.505
Yes, that's-that's what we are.

18:15.678 --> 18:16.888
We're civilized men.

18:16.889 --> 18:19.341
So wait, we're still short $3,500.

18:19.475 --> 18:21.476
- Yeah.
- Can we grab it from an ATM?

